This paper is organised as follows. Section
				2 introduces the ATLAS detector. The simulated Monte Carlo events used in this work are described in Sect.
				3. Section
				4 contains the description of the objects reconstructed in the detector which are key inputs to flavour-tagging algorithms, while Sects.
				5 and
				6 describe the low- and high-level tagging algorithms respectively. Finally, their performance, evaluated on simulated event samples, is presented in Sect.
				7.

