ATLAS uses a right-handed coordinate system with its origin at the nominal interaction point (IP) in the centre of the detector and the
					z-axis along the beam pipe. The
					x-axis points from the IP to the centre of the LHC ring, and the
					y-axis points upwards. Cylindrical coordinates




